{
  "stem": "1721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 319.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother, at that time, thought that I should start a formal schooling.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she sent me to a local grade school outside of the DP camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was called-- I don't remember the school, but the name of the town was Deggendorf, which was a few kilometers south of Munich.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the sheer stupidity of sending a Jewish kid to an all goyam school in Munich, outside of Munich, I don't know where her head was at.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we just came from this whole horrible experience, and she sent me to school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And obviously I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They knew exactly the first day I walked in who I was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, it's not like I was an observant Jew and I had-- was wearing a kippah.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they knew I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And for every day I would get beat up by all these kids.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They just-- these kids my age would just gang up on me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I would come home every day bloodied.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I tried to convince my mother that this was not a place for me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Besides not learning anything, I was scared to death to go into that school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she kept sending me, kept sending me to that school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Whether she wanted to get me out of my hair, but there was no schooling for kids in that camp, in that DP camp, in that displaced person camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was basically-- it wasn't set up for that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was sort of like a way station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So every parent had to make the decision on their own of what they were going to do with their school age children.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she decided to send me to school.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
